definition: master/qualified worker/respectful form of address for older men/CL:個|个[ge4],位[wei4],名[ming2]

sentences.english: Sir, what kind of work in the production process suits me best?
sentences.chinese: 那師傅你覺得我最適合做哪道工序呢？

sentences.english: Liddy, the master's great-granddaughter, was about Bathsheba's equal in age.
sentences.chinese: 麗蒂是作坊師傅的重孫女，和巴絲謝芭年齡相仿。

sentences.english: See the two men to escape, Li master by telephone to the police report to the police.
sentences.chinese: 見兩名男子逃跑後，李師傅借電話向警方報警。

sentences.english: He was apprenticed to a master silversmith.
sentences.chinese: 他跟銀匠師傅拜師學藝。

sentences.english: Ma Long is taking intimate letter put up for the night ripely temple, by discovery of master sea empty rabbi.
sentences.chinese: 馬龍帶着密函投宿圓通寺，被師傅海空法師發現。

sentences.english: It took Mr. Wang about three hours to put the TV set right yesterday.
sentences.chinese: 昨天王師傅花了大約三個小時才把那臺電視機修好。

sentences.english: Master, Don't trust that ape. The brother monkey is deliberately trying to trick you by magic way.
sentences.chinese: 師傅不要信那猴頭，這是猴哥使的障眼法來騙您的。

sentences.english: The little bonzer became the master's inheritor later.
sentences.chinese: 後來，這位小和尚成了師傅的衣鉢傳人。

sentences.english: What about a good Volvo mechanic?
sentences.chinese: 滿意的沃爾沃修車師傅呢？

sentences.english: Why didn’t you have the butcher cut off the end?
sentences.chinese: 他的悍妻尖叫，“你怎麼不叫肉師傅把尾端給切掉？”

sentences.english: Master Wang is the leader of the Hong Men, a group which is noted for its kungfu skills.
sentences.chinese: 王進發師傅是洪門的山主，該門派以其功夫技巧聞名。

sentences.english: These veteran craftsmen have undertaken to train a group of young workers.
sentences.chinese: 這些老手工藝師傅負責培養一批青年工人。

sentences.english: Master Chen was found in a pawn shop them.
sentences.chinese: 後來陳師傅在當鋪裏發現了它們。

sentences.english: The desk was made by Master Wang.
sentences.chinese: 這張課桌是王師傅做的。

sentences.english: Check this out. This is Kung Chang, right?
sentences.chinese: 看看這個，這是吳剛師傅，對吧？

sentences.english: Master Shifu tries his best to train the panda into a real warrior according to Master Wugu's instruction.
sentences.chinese: 師傅謹遵烏龜的教誨，努力將熊貓培養成真正的武士。

definition: used for 師傅|师傅 (in Taiwan)/master/qualified worker
senior male fellow student or apprentice/son (older than oneself) of one's teacher
to help/to lend a hand/to do a favor/to do a good turn
to study at the same school/fellow student/classmate/CL:位[wei4],個|个[ge4]
